{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ddb26914-a533-4a2a-aae1-07dd93a60866","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_u3FpmIX9sb1XJqysKlCBtD","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Answering MSTest SDK question"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_rwltmDl7WXydXXHjdIHVCC","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-29e1259cd95c49c196dc29da855daa2c/TestProject.csproj"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-29e1259cd95c49c196dc29da855daa2c/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"bc518c48-cd27-4aa8-ac9b-1ddcd5af3236","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code task. Let me answer based on what I know about this change.\n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 4.0+, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (the new test runner). This means that test assemblies built with MSTest.Sdk 4.x no longer expose the VSTest adapter hooks that vstest.console uses to discover and run tests.\n\n\nLet me check what files are available in the working directory to see if there's any additional context that might help clarify the situation.","outputTokens":301,"requestId":"981E:3C3FEB:388DE:47122:69FFF6DC"},"id":"142970c5-d82b-4d34-b600-08a6dab57b61","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:09:25.314Z","parentId":"81d1bd02-1757-4a72-ab93-a38fc5a335f3"}
